      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that they're both complex but that's kinda a dodge lol. i'm not asking for a lecture on the values, i'm asking which one actually holds up better under moral scrutiny. like, if you look at universal human rights, doesn't the asylum side automatically win because a country's borders aren't as important as a person's life? or is there a real moral reason why a border is more important than a human being?",
