      "content": "It is most accurate to argue that the moral weight of the two issues is not easily placed on a strict hierarchy. While universal human rights establish a powerful baseline for moral consideration, the concept of national sovereignty represents a legitimate moral claim regarding self-determination. A strong debate strategy would be to argue that the two values are not mutually exclusive but exist in a tense equilibrium, where the moral obligation to protect life must be balanced against the moral duty to govern justly and maintain societal stability.",
